body_html:
Good day for everyone
if I use --model_dir=/inception
everything works well

but I have the same problem of using imagenet on Android Studio java project
I retrain the model with help of imagenet
python retrain.py
--image_dir /tf_images
--architecture mobilenet_1.0_224
--output_graph=/tf/retrained_graph.pb
--output_labels=/tf/retrained_labels.txt

and add retrained_graph.pb to /assets/ of android studio and get such result during debug:

java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Tried to explicitly squeeze dimension 1 but dimension was not 1: 2
W/System.err: [[Node: MobilenetV1/Logits/SpatialSqueeze = SqueezeT=DT_FLOAT, squeeze_dims=[1, 2], _device="/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/cpu:0"]]
W/System.err:

it is look like using of wrong parameters
is anybody knows the right decision?

body:
Good day for everyone
if I use   --model_dir=/inception
everything works well


but I have the same problem of using imagenet on Android Studio java project
I retrain the model with help of imagenet
python retrain.py \
 --image_dir /tf_images \
 --architecture mobilenet_1.0_224 \
  --output_graph=/tf/retrained_graph.pb \
  --output_labels=/tf/retrained_labels.txt

and add retrained_graph.pb to /assets/ of android studio and get such result during debug:

java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Tried to explicitly squeeze dimension 1 but dimension was not 1: 2
W/System.err: 	 [[Node: MobilenetV1/Logits/SpatialSqueeze = Squeeze[T=DT_FLOAT, squeeze_dims=[1, 2], _device="/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/cpu:0"](MobilenetV1/Logits/Conv2d_1c_1x1/BiasAdd)]]
W/System.err:     

it is look like using of wrong parameters
is anybody knows the right decision?
